DIV1.P:
This same Prelate not being in a Capacity to attend himself at the Ordination of En∣cas, chosen Bishop of Paris, dispatched away one of his Priests as a Delegate to represent him, with a Letter importing his Consent unto the Ordination of that Bishop; but upon Condition that he should declare by his Subscription, that he held entirely to the Doctrine of the holy Fathers touching Grace; and to that of the Four Chapters (as they are called) and in one of these Four Chapters, we have these remarkable Words;
That we believe & acknowledge, that by a deep and unsearchable Counsel of

Almighty God, there are some who are predestined unto Life before all Time by the entirely free Mercy of God; and that there are others, who by an incomprehen∣sible Justice, are predestinated to Torments.
